# Outside Inn Radio — Master Setup Guide
**Outside Inn Studios | March 2026 | Personal AI Project Reference**

> Full documentation of how the Outside Inn 24/7 lo-fi radio was built, configured, and launched. Includes all credentials, commands, decisions, and operational procedures.

---

## What This Is

A 24/7 lo-fi radio stream running on a DigitalOcean VPS, pushing a looping video file via FFmpeg directly to YouTube's Outside Inn channel (`@the_outside_inn`). It runs completely unattended — no laptop required, no manual intervention, auto-restarts on any failure, survives VPS reboots.

```
VPS (FFmpeg loop) ──RTMPS──▶ YouTube @the_outside_inn (24/7)
```

---

## Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Choice | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| Restream vs direct YouTube | Direct YouTube | Restream was the failure point on the 151-hour E.I. Werner broadcast. Removing it eliminates one failure point and one monthly cost. |
| tmux + shell loop vs systemd | systemd service | Systemd survives reboots, restarts automatically, logs to journald, never requires SSH to manage. |
| Default stream key vs Scheduled Stream | Scheduled Stream + dedicated key | Default stream key has phantom streaming issue on reconnects >30s. Scheduled Stream with Auto-Start reconnects cleanly every time. |
| RTMP vs RTMPS | RTMPS | Encrypted ingest. YouTube recommends it. Zero cost difference. |
| Re-encode on VPS vs stream copy | Stream copy (`-c:v copy -c:a copy`) | Source file already meets YouTube specs exactly. Stream copy uses near-zero CPU on a $6/mo VPS. |

