## Environment File

**Path:** `/etc/outside-inn-radio.env`
**Permissions:** 600 (root read/write only)

```
YT_INGEST_URL=rtmps://a.rtmps.youtube.com/live2
YT_STREAM_KEY=qvv0-8ugj-3hy0-66f5-9vgg
```

---

## Systemd Service File

**Path:** `/etc/systemd/system/outside-inn-radio.service`

```ini
[Unit]
Description=Outside Inn 24/7 Lo-Fi Radio
After=network-online.target
Wants=network-online.target
StartLimitIntervalSec=600
StartLimitBurst=10

[Service]
Type=simple
EnvironmentFile=/etc/outside-inn-radio.env
ExecStartPre=/usr/bin/test -r /root/HoldtLoop.mp4
ExecStart=/usr/bin/ffmpeg -nostdin -hide_banner -loglevel warning -nostats -re -stream_loop -1 -i /root/HoldtLoop.mp4 -c:v copy -c:a copy -flvflags no_duration_filesize -f flv ${YT_INGEST_URL}/${YT_STREAM_KEY}
Restart=always
RestartSec=5
RestartSteps=5
RestartMaxDelaySec=60
StandardOutput=journal
StandardError=journal

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

### What each line does

| Line | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `After=network-online.target` / `Wants=network-online.target` | Don't start FFmpeg until network is up. Critical on VPS reboots. |
| `StartLimitIntervalSec=600` / `StartLimitBurst=10` | Allows up to 10 restarts in 600 seconds before systemd gives up. Without this, systemd silently stops retrying after 5 failures in 10 seconds — stream dies with no recovery. |
| `EnvironmentFile=` | Loads stream key from protected file. Key never appears in `systemctl status` output. |
| `ExecStartPre=` | Pre-flight check — fails immediately with a clear error if video file is missing, rather than mysterious FFmpeg errors. |
| `-nostdin` | Required for headless operation. Without it, FFmpeg can hang waiting for terminal input. |
| `-hide_banner -loglevel warning -nostats` | Suppresses FFmpeg's startup banner and per-frame progress output. Without this, journald fills up within days. |
| `-re` | Throttles FFmpeg to real-time playback speed. Without it, FFmpeg reads the file as fast as disk allows and floods the RTMP server. |
| `-stream_loop -1` | Loops the file infinitely. |
| `-c:v copy -c:a copy` | Stream copy — no re-encoding. Near-zero CPU usage. Safe only because source file already meets YouTube specs. |
| `-flvflags no_duration_filesize` | Suppresses noisy FLV header warnings on every disconnect. |
| `-f flv` | Required output container format for RTMP/RTMPS. |
| `Restart=always` | Restarts on any exit, including clean exits (FFmpeg exits with code 0 on RTMP disconnect — `on-failure` would NOT catch this). |
| `RestartSec=5` / `RestartSteps=5` / `RestartMaxDelaySec=60` | Exponential backoff — starts at 5s, ramps to 60s over 5 cycles. Fast recovery for glitches, not hammering YouTube during sustained outages. |

