## Updating the Video File

```bash
# 1. Stop the service
systemctl stop outside-inn-radio

# 2. Upload new file from Windows PowerShell
scp D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtLoop.mp4 root@138.197.9.139:/root/HoldtLoop.mp4

# 3. Restart
systemctl start outside-inn-radio
systemctl status outside-inn-radio
```

---

## Rotating the Stream Key

```bash
# 1. Get new key from YouTube Studio → Outside Inn → stream key → rotate icon
# 2. Update env file on VPS
nano /etc/outside-inn-radio.env
# Update YT_STREAM_KEY value

# 3. Restart service
systemctl restart outside-inn-radio
systemctl status outside-inn-radio
```

---

## Auto-Restart Behavior

| Event | What happens |
|---|---|
| YouTube drops connection | FFmpeg exits → restarts in 5s |
| FFmpeg crashes | Restarts in 5s |
| Rapid failures (bad key, network down) | Backoff ramps from 5s to 60s over 5 cycles |
| VPS reboots | Service starts automatically on boot |
| Manual stop | Stays stopped until you run `systemctl start` |
| FFmpeg hangs (rare) | Does NOT auto-restart — systemd only restarts on process exit. Fix: `systemctl restart outside-inn-radio` |

---

## Troubleshooting

### Stream not appearing on YouTube
1. `systemctl status outside-inn-radio` — is it running?
2. `journalctl -u outside-inn-radio -f` — any errors?
3. Check stream key in `/etc/outside-inn-radio.env`
4. In YouTube Studio, confirm you're viewing the "Outside Inn Radio" stream key, not Default stream

### Service fails to start
```bash
journalctl -u outside-inn-radio --no-pager -n 50
```
Most common causes: wrong stream key, or video file missing.

### Service stopped restarting on its own
```bash
systemctl status outside-inn-radio
# If shows "failed":
systemctl reset-failed outside-inn-radio
systemctl start outside-inn-radio
```

### FFmpeg not found
```bash
which ffmpeg
apt update && apt install ffmpeg -y
```

