## Asset Validation Commands (for future reference)

Run these on Windows before uploading any new HoldtLoop.mp4:

```powershell
# Video codec/profile/framerate
ffprobe -v error -show_streams -select_streams v:0 D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtLoop.mp4

# Audio codec/samplerate/channels
ffprobe -v error -show_streams -select_streams a:0 D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtLoop.mp4

# Keyframe timestamps (should be 0, 2, 4, 6, 8...)
ffprobe -v error -select_streams v:0 -show_frames -show_entries frame=pict_type,pts_time -of csv D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtLoop.mp4 | Select-String "I" | Select-Object -First 5
```

Required values:
| Field | Required |
|---|---|
| `codec_name` (video) | `h264` |
| `profile` | `High` |
| `r_frame_rate` | `6/1` |
| `pix_fmt` | `yuv420p` |
| `codec_name` (audio) | `aac` |
| `profile` (audio) | `LC` |
| `sample_rate` | `44100` or `48000` |
| `channel_layout` | `stereo` |
| Keyframe interval | Every 2 seconds |

If anything fails, re-encode before uploading:
```powershell
ffmpeg -i D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtLoop.mp4 `
  -c:v libx264 -profile:v high -g 12 -keyint_min 12 -pix_fmt yuv420p `
  -c:a aac -ar 44100 -ac 2 `
  D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtLoop_fixed.mp4
```

